                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/4610: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Palmer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Beirut</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-12T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 12, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 6:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>52. General Fourgère has arrived from France by airplane via Naples and Athens to
                    relieve General Massiet who is to leave for France with General
                    Mittelhauser.</p>
                <pb facs="0912" n="900" xml:id="pg_900"/>
                <p>Admiral Gouton has arrived to relieve Admiral de Carpentier who has completed a
                    normal 2-year tour of duty at this naval base.</p>
                <p>French steamer from Egypt with officers and men of the French naval forces to be
                    returned to France arrived here this morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Palmer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
